<summary>
The <strong><c>width</c></strong> CSS property sets an element&amp;apos;s width. By default, it sets the width of the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_box_model/Introduction_to_the_CSS_box_model#content_area">content area</see>, but if <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/box-sizing">box-sizing</see> is set to <c>border-box</c>, it sets the width of the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_box_model/Introduction_to_the_CSS_box_model#border_area">border area</see>.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>EmbedInteractiveExample("pages/css/width.html")</para><para>The specified value of <c>width</c> applies to the content area so long as its value remains within the values defined by <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/min-width">min-width</see> and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/max-width">max-width</see>.</para>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_box_model/Introduction_to_the_CSS_box_model">The box model</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/height">height</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/box-sizing">box-sizing</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/min-width">min-width</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/max-width">max-width</see><br/>-The mapped logical properties: <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/block-size">block-size</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/inline-size">inline-size</see><br/></para>
